But his conception of atoms implied, as we shall see in 11, their racing through space at an enormous uniform speed in parallel right lines in one direction, with the curicus exception ex- plained 11 216 foll. This inherent motion both Epicurus and Lucr. understand as a motion downwards: they had no other conception of downwards in space.
